content:
Check:
  all:
    - name: --ORRES
      operator: not_matches_regex
      value: ^[+-]?([0-9]*[.])?[0-9]
    - name: --STRESN
      operator: non_empty
Core:
  Id: CDISC.SENDIG.91
  Version: '1'
  Status: Draft
Description: When --ORRES is representing numeric data with special characters like
  '<' and '>', , --STRESN may not be populated.
Outcome:
  Message: --STRESN may not be populated as --ORRES does not represent a pure numeric
    value
  Output Variables:
    - --ORRES
    - --STRESN
Rule Type: Record Data
Sensitivity: Record
Authorities:
  - Organization: CDISC
    Standards:
      - Name: SENDIG
        Version: '3.1'
        References:
          - Origin: SDTM and SENDIG Conformance Rules
            Rule Identifier:
              Id: '91'
              Version: '1'
            Version: '2.0'
            Citations:
              - Cited Guidance: If numeric data are collected with characters attached
                  (e.g., >, <) no data value should be populated in --STRESN
                Document: IG v3.1
                Section: 4.5.1.1
Scope:
  Classes:
    Include:
      - FINDINGS
  Domains:
    Include:
      - ALL

json.Description: When --ORRES is representing numeric data with special characters like '<' and '>', , --STRESN may not be populated.
